HEADWORD: Juncus
<hw>Juncus</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>The type genus of the
<fam>Juncaceae</fam>, comprising the rushes; they are perennial tufted
glabrous marsh plants of temperate regions.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Juncus</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
